body:
This would allow Yosys to do SAT-based optimisation of netlists with whiteboxes. Consider the following example:

```verilog
(* whitebox *)
module NAND(input a, b, output q);
	assign q = ~(a & b);
endmodule

module top(input a, b, output p, q);
	wire x;
	NAND n1(a, a, x);
	NAND n2(x, x, p);
	NAND n3(b, 1'b0, q);
endmodule
```

`freduce` (or perhaps with a flag like `freduce -wb`) should optimise the NANDs, and `sat -prove q 1` should succeed

